# pi-runner config — COPY to pi-runner/.env. NEVER commit the real .env. WIRING ONLY.
#
# There is NO credential here. The model + API key live ONCE in pi's own machine-global config,
# ~/.pi/agent/models.json (provider "cp"), which pi resolves natively for EVERY project — no key
# per repo, no provider extension, no env. Set that up once per machine (see models.json.example +
# reference/provider-and-headless.md); this file then only points the driver at THIS repo's workflow.
#
# This .env is the only per-repo surface: run.mjs / extract.mjs are byte-identical across every repo
# (and the global-skill template), so a fix to one is a one-file copy.

# ── Wiring (point the generic driver at THIS repo's workflow) ──────────────────────────────
# PI_RUNNER_ROOT defaults to pi-runner/'s parent dir — usually correct, leave unset.
# PI_RUNNER_CWD + PI_RUNNER_WORKFLOW take paths RELATIVE TO ROOT (or absolute).
PI_RUNNER_CWD=.                                    # where pi runs (npm-scripts dir); e.g. a subpackage
PI_RUNNER_WORKFLOW=.claude/workflows/CHANGEME.js   # the workflow .js this repo drives
# PI_RUNNER_UNTIL=design                           # optional default --until during bring-up
# PI_RUNNER_NODE_TIMEOUT=1800                       # optional default node hard-kill seconds (--node-timeout overrides; raise for long build/render nodes)
# PI_RUNNER_REPEAT_KILL=400                          # stuck-loop guard: kill a node after N consecutive identical deltas (0 disables; legit nodes never exceed ~2)
# PI_RUNNER_WORKTREE=1                               # physical isolation: run EACH run in its own git worktree (branch pi/<id>) so concurrent runs can't see/clobber each other. Same as --worktree. Needs committed shared code + inputs passed via --arg/--brief. See reference/worktree-isolation.md.

# ── Model override (OPTIONAL) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The model defaults to provider "cp"'s first entry in ~/.pi/agent/models.json. Pin a different one
# for this repo only by uncommenting (must be an id present in models.json):
# PI_CP_MODEL=qwen3.7-plus
